reviewText: This was a great course getting into the practical domain of the computational biology side. The lecturer was great. But certain topics were brief and the practical assessment test was more focused on different languages like R, JSON, Python and many more. So it is not possible to be jack of all trades. Also everything was perfectly woven with the LINCS project. Kudos to everyone involved in the project.

This course provides a great overview of the BD2K-LINCS program and demonstrates that it's possible to combine multiple (not very related datasets) to bring new biological insights. Some of these concepts are directly relevant to my job. I am giving only 4 stars because is seems to me that  some later parts of the course are not fully relevant to the overall topic. It would be also very useful to provide several "success stories" how the data was used to; for example, initiate drug discovery.
